				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Another major issue is that the costumes in MM NES were heavily modified to simplify them - in the original version, each costume is divided into several sections (head, arms, legs, etc.) which are animated independently, but the NES version had to shrink them down to single units. As a result, costume animations involving individual limbs wouldn't quite work properly.
<br />
<br />There's also the issue that the MM NES engine can only support <strong>four</strong> actors in a room at one time, which might not be quite enough for Zak McKracken.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
